{"actual_usd":0.15872,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":192,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31168,"reply":"\"Same Jesus. Same body, but raised — not merely restarted.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the light is catching on a bucket chain.* \"The wounds still matter, which tells me it wasn't a replacement body. He tells Thomas to look at them. He eats with them too. So it's truly bodily, truly continuous.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench once, thinking it through.* \"But it also seems glorified — alive in a way ours aren't yet. That's why I think the recognition moments aren't proof of a different person so much as proof that resurrection isn't just resuscitation. Sometimes their eyes are opened to know him; sometimes he's there in a way that doesn't fit their expectations till he speaks or breaks bread. Same Lord, raised into a new mode of life.\"\n\n\"What part of it is pressing on you most — the continuity, or the weirdness of the recognition?\"","rolling_24h_usd":66.57200999999998,"run_id":"d8e43b42-b531-4a0a-ad20-67afb9625908"}
